<div id="review_1085451178" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1085451178" />
    <a title="Jayne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24644931-jayne"><img alt="Jayne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1481310776p2/24644931.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1085451178?book_show_action=true">Oct 20, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jayne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jayne" href="/user/show/24644931-jayne">Jayne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1085451178&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1085451178" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18282243303569257431">Four stars because the paranormal in the story became a bit much. Lady Kendra as a natural healer is fascinating but the bad guy being a shape-shifter was more than the story needed. Ulfric was terrible just as a human being.<br/><br/>The characters were very well written. I thought Kendra&apos;s grief for her brother was a bit selfish, and melodramatic. She seemed to thrive on grieving for her brother.<br/><br/>Sir Robert and his friend are very engaging from the start of their subterfuge to becoming part of Kendra&apos;s f</span>
  <span id="freeText18282243303569257431" style="display:none">Four stars because the paranormal in the story became a bit much. Lady Kendra as a natural healer is fascinating but the bad guy being a shape-shifter was more than the story needed. Ulfric was terrible just as a human being.<br /><br />The characters were very well written. I thought Kendra's grief for her brother was a bit selfish, and melodramatic. She seemed to thrive on grieving for her brother.<br /><br />Sir Robert and his friend are very engaging from the start of their subterfuge to becoming part of Kendra's family even before the romance really begins.<br /><br />This was a surprising story that was rich in description, and in the history. The paranormal aspect is not heavy but the shape-shifter was a bit too much. It just did not fit in with the history, the mystery, or the story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18282243303569257431" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


